<div id="review_2258508089" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2258508089" />
    <a title="Linda Dobinson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32368211-linda-dobinson"><img alt="Linda Dobinson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1403100778p2/32368211.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2258508089?book_show_action=true">Mar 07, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Linda Dobinson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Linda Dobinson" href="/user/show/32368211-linda-dobinson">Linda Dobinson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781906462024" href="/book/show/2277185.Miss_Pettigrew_Lives_for_a_Day">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32368211-linda-dobinson?shelf=favourite-classics">favourite-classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32368211-linda-dobinson?shelf=modern-classics">modern-classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2258508089" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9434594002593353602">Miss Pettigrew Lives for a Day is a delightful story that is very much of its day. I absolutely loved it.<br/>It can be described as a Cinderella story though Delysia LaFosse and Edythe Dubarry are reversals of the ugly sisters.<br/>As the title suggests the action takes place over the course of one day. Each chapter covers a few hours so the pace is fast.<br/>Guinevere Pettigrew is a forty year old spinster who had led a drab, malnourished existence as a not-very-good governess. Terrorised by employers and ch</span>
  <span id="freeText9434594002593353602" style="display:none">Miss Pettigrew Lives for a Day is a delightful story that is very much of its day. I absolutely loved it.<br />It can be described as a Cinderella story though Delysia LaFosse and Edythe Dubarry are reversals of the ugly sisters.<br />As the title suggests the action takes place over the course of one day. Each chapter covers a few hours so the pace is fast.<br />Guinevere Pettigrew is a forty year old spinster who had led a drab, malnourished existence as a not-very-good governess. Terrorised by employers and charges alike she is now on the threshold of destitution. The one bright spot in her life is her ''weekly orgy at the cinema'' (p3).<br />When she arrives at 5, Onslow Mansions to apply for yet another dismal position she is shocked when the woman who answers the door is not a bad tempered matron but a ''creature...so lovely she called to mind immediately the beauties of the screen'' (p3).<br />Miss Pettigrew has two sides to her character. The prim and proper moral side that comes from being the daughter of a curate who thought make-up was the ''road to damnation'' (p73), and a repressed fun, naughty side that likes movies her parents would have disapproved of. As she enters Miss LaFosse's flat these two side battle as she notes the pictures on the walls are ''not quite decent'' (p4), yet she feels ''a strange kind of excitement'' (P5).<br />Unlike the people she has come across all her life, Delysia and her friend Edythe treat Miss Pettigrew kindly and as an equal. So do their lovers by not subjecting her to the ''polite, excluding courtesies that had been her measure from men all her life '' (9).<br />As the day develops so does Miss Pettigrew's fun side as she abandons many of her former beliefs and gives herself up wholeheartedly to her new friends who appreciate her worth.<br />I recommend this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9434594002593353602" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


