<div id="review_3151130018" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3151130018" />
    <a title="Antoinette" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5328952-antoinette"><img alt="Antoinette" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1503842818p2/5328952.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3151130018?book_show_action=true">Feb 17, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Antoinette" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Antoinette" href="/user/show/5328952-antoinette">Antoinette</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5328952-antoinette?shelf=british-literature">british-literature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5328952-antoinette?shelf=persephone-edition">persephone-edition</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3151130018" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5989370353017648382">“A knock on Miss LaFosse’s door would mean excitement, drama, a new crisis to b e dealt with. Oh, if only for once the Lord would be good and cause some miracle to happen to keep her here, to see for one day how life could be lived, so that for all the rest of her dull, uneventful days, when things grew bad, she could look back in her mind and dwell on the time when for one perfect day she, Miss Pettigrew, lived.”<br/><br/>Imagine living a dreary existence, then one day you are given a magical, beyond you</span>
  <span id="freeText5989370353017648382" style="display:none">“A knock on Miss LaFosse’s door would mean excitement, drama, a new crisis to b e dealt with. Oh, if only for once the Lord would be good and cause some miracle to happen to keep her here, to see for one day how life could be lived, so that for all the rest of her dull, uneventful days, when things grew bad, she could look back in her mind and dwell on the time when for one perfect day she, Miss Pettigrew, lived.”<br /><br />Imagine living a dreary existence, then one day you are given a magical, beyond your dreams day- one you never expected. That’s what happens to Miss Pettigrew, a sad sack, if you will, who has never had much happiness or success in her life. I loved watching Miss Pettigrew blossom over one day. As I was reading, I kept hoping and wishing that she got more than this one day.<br /><br />This is a happy, delightful, charming book. It is very fairy tale like. It put a big smile on my face, so mission accomplished.<br /><br />This is a Persephone book- their goal is to get back into print books that are no longer in print. Their focus is women authors but they also have some male authors. This book was originally published in 1938. I definitely plan to read more of these books.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5989370353017648382" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


