      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/468569.Winifred_Watson">About Winifred Watson</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/468569.Winifred_Watson"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1247268152p3/468569.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/468569.Winifred_Watson">Winifred Watson
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
75
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer13666164273909961611">Winifred Eileen Watson (20 October 1906 - 5 August 2002) was an English writer. She is best known for her novel, <b>Miss Pettigrew Lives for a Day</b>, which was adapted into a major motion picture of the same name (released in 2008).<br/><br/>Bibliography:<br/><em><br/> Fell Top (1935)<br/> Odd Shoes (1936)<br/> Miss Pettigrew Lives for a Day (1938)<br/> Upyonder (1938) <br/> Hop, Step, Jump (1939)<br/> Leave and Bequeath (1943)</em><br/></span>

</div>
</div>

<div class="clear"></div></div></div><div class="bigBoxBottom"></div></div>

  

